`task.last` returns the most recently created task instance (TaskInstance). It is `null` before the first `.perform()` call. Through `task.last`, you can inspect the instance's state (`isRunning`, `isFinished`, `isCanceled`), its resolved `value`, or its `error`. This is the primary way to access results from the last execution.

