`timeout(ms)` from ember-concurrency is a cancelation-aware delay that pauses the task for the specified number of milliseconds. Unlike `new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, ms))`, `timeout()` respects task cancellation ŌĆö if the task is cancelled while waiting, `timeout()` stops immediately, preventing memory leaks.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component'
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking'
import { task, timeout } from 'ember-concurrency'
import { registerDestructor } from '@ember/destroyable'

export default class LiveScorePollerComponent extends Component {
