ember-concurrency uses Glimmer's `@tracked` storage internally for all task state properties (`isRunning`, `isIdle`, `last`, `numRunning`, etc.). When you install ember-concurrency v3+, it hooks into `@glimmer/tracking` primitives so that any template that reads `task.isRunning` automatically re-renders when that value changes. You don't need to manually declare `@tracked isLoading = false` and toggle it ŌĆö the task is its own reactive state machine. This eliminates an entire class of bugs where developers forget to reset loading flags.

```gjs
import Component from '@glimmer/component'
import { task, taskGroup } from 'ember-concurrency'

export default class MatchDataLoader extends Component {
